article.headline: Centenary 83, Chicago St. 80
article.story: SHREVEPORT, La. (AP) -- Nick Stallings had 22 points and Alexander Starr 20 points and 10 rebounds as Centenary edged Chicago State 83-80 on Saturday. Starr also had 10 rebounds for Centenary (10-18), which finished with 29. Chicago State (9-20), was led 24 points from John Cantrell. Kourtney Calvin and David Holston added 16 each, and Royce Parran added 10. Chicago State led 36-32 at halftime. Tyrone Hamilton had 12 points for Centenary, and Chase Adams 11. Centenary was 19-22 from the free throw line, including 6-of-6 from Starr. Hamilton and Lance Hill, who finished with eight points, both were 4-for-4.
